# Security Keyword (clouds-f)

Canonical source: `SKILL.md` in this skill root.

Apply this rule for `security`, `OWASP`, `XSS`, `CSRF`, `auth`, `authz`, `secrets`, and sanitization-related requests.

## Security Rules

1. Treat all external/user-controlled input as untrusted.
2. Validate at boundaries and encode output safely.
3. Verify auth/authz checks and session/token handling paths.
4. Prevent client-side secret exposure.
5. Review dependency and supply-chain risk before adding packages.
6. Keep fixes minimal while preserving existing product behavior.

